706107f-a.text:
Ocean Ave., west side, north from Emmons Ave. At the left, is the new Lundy Bros., eating Palace; in the extreme background, may be seen the steeple of St. Mark's R.C. Church.
August 1, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
706107f-a.folder: Ocean Avenue & Emmons Avenue, Brooklyn, NY

704110f-b.text:
Emmons Avenue, east from near Ocean Avenue, showing the W. P. A. conducting highway operations tn connection with the city's belt parkway system. View 3 shows the north side of the avenue, viewing westward, the building in Spanish architecture being Lundy's Restaurant.

View 1: March 16, 1936
View 2: April 8, 1936
View 3: March 16, 1936
